article.headline: Murray State 73, Belhaven 72
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Bruce Carter scored 20 points and Ed Horton hit a pair of free throws in the final seconds Thursday night to lead Murray State to a 73-72 win over Belhaven. Murray (1-3) trailed 63-55 with 10:34 left in the game on a free throw by Dax Miller, who scored 22 points for Belhaven (3-4), but then went on a 16-7 run to pull ahead 71-70 on a layup by Carter. Bobby Johnson's jumper with 12 seconds left put Belhaven ahead 72-71 lead before Horton's free throws five seconds later gave Murray the final margin. Johnson attempted a jump shot with a second left but missed, leaving Belhaven short. Murray led by as much as 11 points in the first half, 22-11 on a 3-pointer by Tyler Holloway with 10:41 left in the half, but Belhaven fought back to lead 35-32 on a 3-pointer by Iman Walcott with 4:12 to go. The teams then traded baskets until Horton's jumper with three seconds left that gave Murray a 42-40 halftime lead. Horton finished with 13 points for Murray, and Holloway scored 10. Johnson added 14 points for Belhaven, and Jeff Sullivan had 12.
